{{Politics of Nauru}}
A '''constitutional referendum''' was held in [[Nauru]] on 27 February 2010.<ref>{{cite web|author=|url=http://www.rnzi.com/pages/news.php?op=read&id=51785 |title=Nauru Government confident that public will back constitutional reforms |publisher=Rnzi.com |date=2010-02-08 |accessdate=2010-08-21}}</ref> Voters were asked to vote on amendments to the [[Constitution of Nauru|constitution]], most notably a change to a directly elected [[President of Nauru|president]] (instead of one chosen by [[Parliament of Nauru|parliament]]) and a strengthening of human rights legislation (but also a clarification of the distribution of powers and other, less notable amendments).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://australianetworknews.com/stories/201002/2810451.htm?desktop |title=Stories:Nauru to hold constitutional referendum |publisher=Australia Network News |date=2010-02-04 |accessdate=2010-08-21}}</ref> A two-thirds majority was required for the amendments to pass.<ref name="naurugov1">[http://www.naurugov.nr/parliament/projects/constitution/index.html#referendum Constitutional Review Project] Parliament of Nauru</ref>
The referendum was part of a large-scale constitutional renewal; the referendum had to be held to approve changes to some especially protected parts of the constitution, while other changes were made by simple parliamentary vote. Any changes would only take effect on the day of the next general election, likely in May/June 2011.<ref name="naurugov1"/>
Turnout was 78%, with almost 4,400 votes cast; the constitutional changes were rejected by majority of two thirds, almost 3,000 votes.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://australianetworknews.com/stories/201002/2832338.htm?desktop |title=Stories:Changes to Nauru's constitution rejected at referendum |publisher=Australia Network News |date=2010-03-01 |accessdate=2010-08-21}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author=|url=http://www.rnzi.com/pages/news.php?op=read&id=52184 |title=Nauruans vote against proposed Constitutional Amendments |publisher=Rnzi.com |date=2010-02-28 |accessdate=2010-08-21}}</ref> It was considered immediately afterwards whether another referendum might be held at a later time.<ref>{{cite web|author=|url=http://www.rnzi.com/pages/news.php?op=read&id=52201 |title=Nauru leaders disappointed with referendum rebuff |publisher=Rnzi.com |date=2010-03-01 |accessdate=2010-08-21}}</ref>
