'''Soviet–Estonian Non-Aggression Pact''' was a [[non-aggression pact]], signed between the [[Soviet Union]] and [[Estonia]] on May 4, 1932.<ref>[http://www.worldlii.org/int/other/LNTSer/1932/151.html League of Nations Treaty Series, Vol. CXXXI, 1932, pp. 297-307.]</ref> The terms of the treaty were:
Article 1. Each party guarantees the borders of each other, set by the [[Treaty of Tartu (Russian–Estonian)|Treaty of Tartu]], and must not infringe upon each other's borders. Article 2. Each party agrees not to form a coalition against one another, form an alliance against one another, or politically or economically embargo each other.
